{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/secret-of-google-web-based-ocr-service-fe30eecedd01", "time": 1682994633.638703, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/secret-of-google-web-based-ocr-service-fe30eecedd01/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Secret of Google Web-Based OCR Service | by Edward Ma | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Secret of Google Web-Based OCR Service", "description": "Optical Character Recognition (OCR) is one of the way to connect reality world and virtual word. First OCR system is introduced in late 1920s. The objective of OCR is recognising text from image\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract", "anchor_text": "tesseract", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/docs/blob/master/das_tutorial2016/6ModernizationEfforts.pdf", "anchor_text": "sharing", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract/wiki/APIExample", "anchor_text": "C-API in python", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://github.com/madmaze/pytesseract", "anchor_text": "pytesseract", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://cloud.google.com/vision/docs/fulltext-annotations", "anchor_text": "Google Vision API", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "http://medium.com/@makcedward/", "anchor_text": "Medium Blog", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/edwardma1026", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://github.com/makcedward", "anchor_text": "Github", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://arxiv.org/pdf/1708.04671.pdf", "anchor_text": "Sequence-to-Label Script Identification for Multilingual OCR", "paragraph_index": 14}, {"url": "https://makcedward.github.io/", "anchor_text": "https://makcedward.github.io/", "paragraph_index": 16}], "all_paragraphs": ["Optical Character Recognition (OCR) is one of the way to connect reality world and virtual word. First OCR system is introduced in late 1920s. The objective of OCR is recognising text from image. However, it is very challenge to achieve a very high accuracy due to lots of factors. In the following story, I will introduce how Google build solution which is one of the Google Cloud Vision API to tackle this problem.", "Talking about OCR, tesseract is one of the famous open source library that everyone can leverage it to execute OCR. Tesseract is found by HP and development has been sponsored by Google since 2006. Tesseract 3.x model is old version while 4.x version is built by deep learning (LSTM). If you want to understand difference between 3.x and 4.x, you can visit sharing for more detail.", "As tesseract is implemented by C++, we cannot invoke it as other python library. Indeed, we can invoke C-API in python but it is not quite user friendly. Therefore, python wrapper, pytesseract, is introduced to make our life easier.", "Before introducing architecture design, some definitions needed to be introduced.", "Giving a image, it go through 5 stages to get the final result in Google Vision API.", "First step is using Conventional Neural Network (CNN)-based model to detect and localised lines of text and generating a set of bounding boxes.", "Classifies the direction per bounding box. If necessary, some bounding box will be filter out as it is erroneously detected as text.", "Identifies script per bounding box. It is assumes that there is one 1 script per bounding box but allowing multiple scripts per image.", "This is the core part of OCR which is recognising text from image. It does not only include character-based language model but also inception style optical model and custom decoding algorithm.", "Determining reading of order and distinguishing title, headers etc.", "As mentioned before, tesseract is sponsored by Google. I think this is one of the reason why authors compare result with tesseract. Character Error Rate (CER) is adopted for model comparison. It defined as edit distance divided by reference length and scaled by 100. The lower the better.", "Hold one, why does image processing step not include in the pipeline? Paper does not mention about the reason. I believe that it is due to neural network model already able to capture those characterise.", "Besides performance, speed is another consideration. From my experience, Tesseract is doing good in recognising but it is quite slow.", "I am Data Scientist in Bay Area. Focusing on state-of-the-art in Data Science, Artificial Intelligence , especially in NLP and platform related. You can reach me from Medium Blog, LinkedIn or Github.", "Fujii Y., Driesen K., Baccash J., Hurst A., Popat A. C.. 2017. Sequence-to-Label Script Identification for Multilingual OCR.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Focus in Natural Language Processing, Data Science Platform Architecture. https://makcedward.github.io/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ffe30eecedd01&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsecret-of-google-web-based-ocr-service-fe30eecedd01&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsecret-of-google-web-based-ocr-service-fe30eecedd01&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_tex